<variablelist>

	<varlistentry>
	    	<term>viz_cuda</term>
		<listitem>
			<para>
If true then install the nVidia CUDA compilers, libraries, and SDK.  
The viz_nvidia attribute must also be set to true to enable the CUDA driver.
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    	<term>viz_tile_{bottom, top, left, right}_bezel</term>
		<listitem>
			<para>
The height and width in millimeters of the LCD bezels.
To disable bezel hiding set all of these to zero.
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    	<term>viz_tile_{height, width}</term>
		<listitem>
			<para>
The height and width in millimeters of the viewable portion of the LCD
panel.
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    	<term>viz_tile_{horizontal, vertical}_shift</term>
		<listitem>
			<para>
The shift in millimeters applied to a column or row of a wall.  This
is only usefull for walls that are started to sag, or lean in one
direction.  This offset can be used to re-aling the wall into a
rectangle rather than repairing the wall.
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
	    	<term>viz_tile_resolution</term>
		<listitem>
			<para>
The pixel resolution of the tile in the standard X11 format of COLxROW.
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
    		<term>viz_nvidia</term>
		<listitem>
			<para>
If true all host with this attribute will have the nVidia driver
and tools installed.
If the host is already installed this will take affect on the next 
re-installation.  
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry>
    		<term>viz_x11_modules</term>
		<listitem>
			<para>
A space delimited list of X11 module names to be loaded when X11 is
started.
This attribute is used by the "rocks sync tile" command when generating
the xorg.conf file on the tiles.
			</para>
		</listitem>
	</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

